      <section id="id8581121">
        <title>ACTIVITY:To perform mental calculations [LO 1.9.1]</title>
        <para id="id14810055">1. See how many figures you can find in this garden and then add them together. If you work cleverly you will be able to calculate the answers in a flash! Are you able to see how?</para>
        <figure id="id14804434">
          <media id="id14804434_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics1-8b38.png" id="id14804434__onlineimage" height="172" width="319"/>
          </media>
        </figure>
        <para id="id15761216">What is your answer? __________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id13756796">2. Now we are going to test your mental calculation skills in a different way. If you know your multiplication tables and can also add and subtract well, you will not have any trouble. Try to complete these within three minutes:</para>
        <para id="id14809216">2.1 ___________ x 8 = 72 </para>
        <para id="id7901622">2.2 ___________ ÷ 11 = 12 </para>
        <para id="id14778919">2.3 119 + ____________ = 136 </para>
        <para id="id16850639">2.4 _____________ - 214 = 117 </para>
        <para id="id15004772">2.5 Double 249: _________________</para>
        <para id="id15834966">2.6 Halve 137: __________________</para>
        <para id="id15837658">2.7 30 x _______________ = 30 000 </para>
        <para id="id14772673">2.8 4 x 3 x 12 = _______________ </para>
        <para id="id16850977">2.9 567 ______________ 23 = 590</para>
        <para id="id15620764">2.10 8 670 ÷ _____________ = 867</para>
        <para id="id15129402">2.11 (5 x 9) + 18 = _____________</para>
        <para id="id16709503">2.12 (7 + 15) x 8 = ______________</para>
        <para id="id15503987">2.13 (42 ÷ ___________) + 14 = 20</para>
        <para id="id14283062">2.14 (5 x ______________) – 9 = 11</para>
        <para id="id14179740">2.15 Halve x _________________ = 225</para>
        <para id="id15697991">Complete by colouring in the appropriate block:</para>
